race.description: Go Hire The Event People C,G&E Maiden Handicap
race.comment: REWRITE (2) showed good natural speed then fought on well for second on debut last start over 1000m at Hawkesbury. Better for that hit-out and with the winkers on over an extra 200m today he looks a great chance to go one better. SPONARS (3) has raced twice this prep and found the line well to fill a minor placing on each occasion. Gets out over more ground now which is ideal. Beautifully drawn and looms as the obvious threat. PERFECT APPLE (11) raced wide so his tiring ninth when resuming over this distance at Rosehill can be forgiven. Freshened up and from a nice gate this time can improve sharply. AGENT ZERO (12) returns from a five-month spell. Wasn't far off them in the three runs of his maiden campaign. Now a gelding which might be the making of him. SUPERMASSIVE (6) debuts for Waterhouse/Bott. Snitzel gelding who trialled well recently at Randwick. In the mix with the help of a favourable draw.
